                        <interp inst="t18400511-name-765" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MOORE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Peter King Holder, of Great Warner-street, Clerkenwell. On the 11th of May I saw the prisoner take this cotton from the door, and go away with it—I ran round the counter to pursue him, but some young females cried out, "Stop thief," and he dropped the print—he was brought back—I am sure he is the person who took it.</p>
